quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Bestower of unlimited mercy —
  55,2,has taught (to mankind) Al-Quran
  55,3,He created the human being
  55,4,"He taught him Al-Bayan [‘The Explanation (to every query)’"
  55,5,The sun and the moon (move) under a mathematical calculation
  55,6,And the stars and the trees both submit (to the laws of God)
  55,7,"And the heaven: He has raised it high; and He has evolved the balance —"
  55,8,in order that you may not transgress in the weights and measures
  55,9,"And stick to the measures and weights with full justice, and do not make deficient the weights and measures"
  55,10,And the earth — He evolved it for the creatures
  55,11,therein are fruits and date-palms out-growing sheathed fruit-stalks (enclosing the raw-dates)
  55,12,"and the husked grain, and the fragrant scented plant"
  55,13,"Then with what Majesties (Blessings or Favours) of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain (i.e., the jinns and the mankind) shall commit denial"
  55,14,"He created (the first of the) human being from sounding clay, like the clay-pieces of broken pottery"
  55,15,And He created the jinns from a smokeless flame of fire
  55,16,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,17,"Rabb to the two easts, and Rabb to the two wests"
  55,18,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,19,He has made to flow two seas — they meet each other
  55,20,(yet) between those two (exists) a barrier.Both (of them) dishonour (it) not (and thus maintain separate properties and taste of their waters)
  55,21,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,22,Out of those two come out pearls and coral
  55,23,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,24,"And to Him belong the sailing ships in the seas, like mountains"
  55,25,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,26,All that whoever is on this (earth) is one who must perish
  55,27,"and shall abide the Face of your Nourisher-Sustainer, Owner of the Glory and the Honour"
  55,28,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,29,Invokes Him whosoever is in the heavens and the earth. Each and every day He (appears) in a (new) Dimension
  55,30,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,31,Soon We pay you attention O you two burdened groups
  55,32,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,33,"O assembly of the jinns and mankind! If you had the ability that you go beyond the confines of the heavens and the earth, then do go beyond. You shall not go beyond except (when properly equipped) with power"
  55,34,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,35,"There will be sent against you both, a smokeless flame of fire and heated smoke; then you shall not take aid and assistance and defend one another"
  55,36,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,37,So when the heaven has developed cracks and it has become rosy pink like (olive) oil
  55,38,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,39,So this Day no question will be asked to a human being and nor to a jinn about his sin
  55,40,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,41,"The criminals will be recognised by their marks (of disobedience and arrogance), so he will be seized by forelocks and the feet"
  55,42,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,43,This happens to be Hell the criminals denied thereof
  55,44,They will move between it and between hot water — violently boiling
  55,45,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,46,"And for that who realised the Position of his Nourisher-Sustainer, (are ready) two orchards (in Paradise)"
  55,47,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,48,Both possessors of spreading branches
  55,49,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,50,In these two (orchards are) two springs — both flow swiftly
  55,51,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,52,In these two (are available) out of every kind of (wet and dry) fruits — two kinds
  55,53,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,54,"(Those who have entered Paradise are) recliners on the carpets whose under-lining (is made) of silk-brocade; and the product of the two orchards being very close, easy of reach"
  55,55,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,56,In these (are wonderful members of a new creation) who restrain the glance. No human being has become acquainted of them before those (Believers who have been allowed entry in Paradise) and nor a jinn
  55,57,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,58,(In beauty) — as if they (are) the rubies and the corals
  55,59,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,60,What becomes the reward of goodness in excellence except excellent goodness
  55,61,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,62,"And besides these two (orchards, there will be other) two orchards"
  55,63,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,64,Both possessing lush-green appearance
  55,65,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,66,"In these two (latter orchards are) two springs, both gushing forth (their) water"
  55,67,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,68,"In both these orchards (are available dry and wet) fruits, and date-palm and pomegranate"
  55,69,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,70,In these (personalities are ingrained) virtues (and) sincerities
  55,71,"Then with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,72,Hur — restrained personalities within pavilions
  55,73,"Then, with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,74,No human being has become acquainted of them before those (Believers who have been allowed entry in Paradise) and nor a jinn
  55,75,"Then, with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,76,"(The Believers in Paradise are such) who recline on green cushion and on mattress, excellent ones"
  55,77,"Then, with what Majesties of the Nourisher-Sustainer of you two, you twain shall commit denial"
  55,78,"Blessed became the Name of your Rabb, Owner of the Glory and the Honour"